HEADWORD: Footstall
<hw>Foot"stall`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Pedestal</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The stirrup of a woman's
saddle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>The plinth or base of a
pillar.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Footstep</ent>⟦br⟧
